Dewfall: A gift that gives life. I am happy and thankful of the kind of life I have. It is not luxurious but precious. It is a gift from the Father nourished in my mother's womb. Though I can't always get what I want, I am surely well-provided of my needs. I have a family that backs and guides me in everything that I do, as long as it helps me grow. I always feel well-loved by the people who really do, that teaches me to sow love in all the things I do. To care for our common home is one of the things I fell in love with. It is His creation that sustains the life He gave; the life we live. God is love. In order for us to live, we must love. It is not you alone whom He has given life to. So it is important to share that love to those who also live. Good things root from good deeds. Bad things erupt from misdeeds. Surely we have differences, that is how He made us all unique. Out of these differences, let us sow love not hatred, understanding not indifference, unity not divisiveness,
